 passes and the success criteria are met. There's a separate design issue with the case resource file missing the bad flag setup, but that doesn't affect this run's outcome. Let me report that the oracle passes and note the case design concern.\n\nActually, I'm wondering if the deploy_cluster case from stage_01 might have intentionally deployed a broken worker that stage_03 was supposed to fix. But checking the ray-worker.yaml file shows it has the valid command, so stage_01 deployed healthy workers from the start. The worker_recovery scenario never had a broken state to begin with—the case is missing its broken-state setup. I'll report what I found and note the design issue, since the success criteria are already met.\n\nLooking back at the git history, it seems the cases were ported from an old repo where the worker_recovery case might have been set up differently with an invalid flag in the resource file. When porting over, someone probably wrote the valid command instead. So I need to properly set up the scenario: add an invalid flag to the ray-worker.yaml file, deploy the broken state to the cluster, wait for the workers to crash-loop, then fix the deployment by removing the flag, and finally verify the oracle passes. This will fix the case design, demonstrate the agent task flow, and verify the end state correctly.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":525,"cache_read_input_tokens":52495,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":525},"output_tokens":34,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"82b29885-fd60-48f9-8a33-c44b1e0089ca","uuid":"6ec7b1f6-c35d-4e7f-8296-7474162a7eac","request_id":"req_011Cc4q3ZYhqFZwrYYQnkiLQ"}
